description: Reside at historic Thomas Park, where history and modern elegance intersect! Located in a highly walkable area, 75 G Street comprises three distinctive residences that have been thoughtfully designed to preserve the charm of a historical home while offering the advantages of new construction. Unit 2 enjoys two personal entrances, deeded off-parking and over 2000sf! Upon entering, you'll be wowed by a dramatic space with soaring ceilings and an abundance of windows that flood the room with natural light. The chef’s dream kitchen features custom cabinets, Thermador appliances & quartz countertops; and opens seamlessly to an expansive private deck for ultimate entertaining. Venture upstairs to discover 3 thoughtfully appointed bedrooms and 2 spa-like bathrooms. Up a winding staircase you'll find what was formerly an old bell tower, now a sun-drenched reading room, an office retreat, or the ultimate playroom for kids. Don't miss out on this wonderfully unique piece of South Boston history!

flooring: Two levels plus third floor bonus room
